--- MRDS_CO — USGS MINERAL RESOURCE DATA SYSTEM (Colorado) ---
Source: USGS MRDS — Colorado-clipped, category field computed
Style File: MRDS_CO_category.qml
CRS: EPSG:26913
Scale Visibility: ALL rules 1:1,000 – 1:75,000 (field + area planning only)

8 rules — Garmin-optimized symbology (high contrast, simple shapes):

  [1] TIER 1 — ACTIVE MINE / HIGH-VALUE PROSPECT
      Shape  — Star (4 or 5 point)
      Color  — Gold (RGB 255,200,0)
      Outline — near-black (RGB 30,30,30)
      Size   — 4.0mm  (largest symbol on layer)
      Meaning: Active producing mine OR high-confidence prospect with
               known gold, silver, or multi-metal mineralization.
               Priority target for field investigation.

  [2] TIER 2 — PAST PRODUCER
      Shape  — Circle
      Color  — Orange (RGB 255,120,0)
      Outline — near-black
      Size   — 3.0mm
      Meaning: Historic producing mine — ceased operations but indicates
               confirmed mineralization. High prospecting value.

  [3] TAILINGS
      Shape  — Square
      Color  — Brown (RGB 140,90,40)
      Outline — near-black
      Size   — 2.5mm
      Meaning: Tailings deposit — mine waste pile from past processing.
               May indicate nearby workings. Do not disturb (EPA).

  [4] BASE METAL
      Shape  — Circle
      Color  — Teal (RGB 0,200,180)
      Outline — near-black
      Size   — 2.5mm
      Meaning: Lead, zinc, copper, or other base metal occurrence.
               Includes active, prospect, and other base metal sites.

  [5] CRITICAL MINERAL
      Shape  — Diamond
      Color  — Purple (RGB 180,0,255)
      Outline — near-black
      Size   — 2.5mm
      Meaning: Lithium, cobalt, rare earth elements, or other federally
               designated critical minerals.

  [6] GEMSTONE
      Shape  — Diamond
      Color  — Magenta/Hot Pink (RGB 230,0,120)
      Outline — near-black
      Size   — 2.5mm
      Meaning: Gemstone occurrence — aquamarine, topaz, rhodochrosite,
               turquoise, or other collectible minerals.

  [7] URANIUM
      Shape  — Triangle
      Color  — Lime Green (RGB 80,200,0)
      Outline — near-black
      Size   — 2.5mm
      Meaning: Uranium occurrence — Colorado Plateau / sedimentary hosted.
               Informational only.

  [8] UNCLASSIFIED
      Shape  — Circle
      Color  — Grey
      Outline — near-black
      Size   — 1.5mm  (smallest symbol on layer)
      Meaning: Prospect, past producer, or active mine — commodity or
               classification not determined from MRDS data.

Labels:
  Tier 1 site names only (Active Mine + High-Value Prospect)
  Field: site_name
  Font: Arial Bold, 7pt
  Color: dark charcoal (RGB 30,30,30)
  Buffer: white 250,250,250, 0.8mm
  Scale: 1:1,000 – 1:15,000 (close field only)
  Placement: over/near point, quadrant offset
  Overlap handling: PreventOverlap, duplicate suppression enabled
  All other categories: no labels (symbol only)

IMPORTANT NOTE:
  Industrial and noise categories (coal, construction aggregate, etc.)
  have been deliberately excluded. This layer shows only prospects and
  mines relevant to self-guided recreational prospecting.

