--- OWNERSHIP ---
Source: Compiled Colorado land ownership — BLM, USFS, NPS, State, Private
Style File: Ownership_CO_Style.qml
CRS: EPSG:26913

4 rules — polygon fills with labeling:

  [1] PROHIBITED — NO COLLECTING / NO ENTRY
      Fill  — Red (RGB 200,70,70)
      Outline — dark red (RGB 140,30,30)
      Covers: National Parks (NPS), designated Wilderness Areas,
              Wilderness Study Areas (WSA), Private land
      Meaning: Prospecting and rock collecting strictly prohibited.
               No entry without authorization. Fines and criminal
               penalties apply in NPS and Wilderness.

  [2] VERIFY — CHECK RULES BEFORE ENTRY
      Fill  — Gold/Amber (RGB 220,180,60)
      Outline — dark gold (RGB 160,120,20)
      Covers: State land (SLB), Colorado Parks & Wildlife (CPW),
              Areas of Critical Environmental Concern (ACEC)
      Meaning: Entry and collecting may be restricted or require permit.
               Always verify current rules with managing agency before
               prospecting. Rules vary by parcel.

  [3] OPEN — PROSPECTING GENERALLY PERMITTED
      Fill  — Green (RGB 100,180,100)
      Outline — dark green (RGB 60,120,60)
      Covers: BLM General Use land, USFS General Forest land
      Meaning: Recreational prospecting and collecting generally allowed
               under standard rules (personal use quantities,
               no mechanized excavation without permit, no sale).
               Verify no special closures before visiting.

  [4] UNKNOWN — VERIFY BEFORE ENTRY
      Fill  — Lavender/Grey-Purple (RGB 180,160,200)
      Outline — grey-purple
      Meaning: Ownership not determined or data gap. Do not assume
               access is permitted. Verify parcel ownership before
               entering or collecting.

