SECTION 10 — PROSPECTING ACCESS DECISION TREE
================================================================================

  Step 1 — Check OWNERSHIP layer color at target location:
           RED    = Stop. Prohibited. Do not enter for collecting.
           GOLD   = Verify with agency before going.
           GREEN  = Generally open — confirm no special closures.
           PURPLE = Unknown — verify parcel ownership first.

  Step 2 — Check MRDS_CO sites in area:
           Gold Star (4mm)  = Tier 1 priority — investigate
           Orange circle    = Past producer — confirmed mineralization
           Teal/Purple/etc. = Secondary targets by commodity

  Step 3 — Check MINERAL REGIONS overlay:
           Gold fill = High/moderate potential zone confirmation

  Step 4 — Check GEOLOGY overlay:
           Cenozoic (green) + Intrusive (purple) = Epithermal/Porphyry context
           Precambrian (teal) = Lode district basement context
           Mesozoic (red) = Uranium-vanadium sedimentary context

  Step 5 — Plan ROUTE using transport hierarchy:
           Highway → Major Road → Backcountry Road (OML 3+) → 4WD/Trail
           Avoid Closed (red) roads entirely.
           Check BLM Gates — may be seasonally locked.

